Adapter Pattern — One Line
Converts one interface into another that client expects
🔥 Core Idea
Incompatible → Compatible (via Adapter)
⚡ Real-Life Intuition
🔌 Plug & Socket Adapter
4
🧠 Mapping
Client → Plug  
Existing System → Socket  
Adapter → Converter
🔥 Structure (MOST IMPORTANT)
Components
Client → calls Target interface

Target → expected interface

Adapter → implements Target + uses Adaptee

Adaptee → existing incompatible class
Visual Flow
Client → Adapter → Adaptee
🧠 Aha Line
Adapter = Translator between two systems
💻 Your Example (Weight Machine)
Problem
Existing → Pounds  
Client → Kilograms
Solution
Adapter converts pounds → kg
Code Flow
Adaptee (Existing)
class WeightMachine {
    double getWeightInPounds() {
        return 28;
    }
}
Target (Expected)
interface WeightMachineAdapter {
    double getWeightInKg();
}
Adapter
class WeightMachineAdapterImpl implements WeightMachineAdapter {

    private WeightMachine machine;

    public double getWeightInKg() {
        double pounds = machine.getWeightInPounds();
        return pounds * 0.45;
    }
}
Client
adapter.getWeightInKg();
🧠 What Happened Internally
Client → Adapter (asks for KG)
Adapter → Adaptee (gets Pounds)
Adapter → converts → returns KG
🔥 Real Industry Examples
1️⃣ API Response Transformation
External → XML  
Your system → JSON  
Adapter → converts XML → JSON
2️⃣ Third-party Integration
Payment Gateway A → format A  
Your system → format B  
Adapter handles mapping
3️⃣ Spring Boot (Hidden Usage)
@RequestBody → Object mapping  
DTO ↔ Entity conversion
🔥 When to Use (INTERVIEW GOLD)
✔ Interfaces don’t match
✔ Reuse existing class without modifying it
✔ Third-party integration
✔ Legacy system integration
✔ Data format conversion
❌ When NOT to Use
❌ If you can change original class
❌ If no incompatibility exists
🔥 Adapter vs Decorator (IMPORTANT)
Adapter
Changes interface
Decorator
Adds behavior
Shortcut
Adapter → Convert  
Decorator → Enhance
🔥 Adapter vs Proxy
Adapter
Fix incompatibility
Proxy
Control access
🧠 Quick Comparison Table
Pattern	Purpose
Adapter	Convert interface
Decorator	Add functionality
Proxy	Control access
🎯 Interview Answer
Definition
Adapter pattern converts the interface of a class into another interface that clients expect.
Real Example
XML → JSON converter
Key Benefit
Reuse existing code without modifying it
🧠 Final Intuition
If two systems can't talk → use Adapter
🔥 Ultimate Aha
Adapter = Compatibility Layer